        : m_x { x }
        , m_y { y }
    {
    }Our recommendation is to use the third style above:Put the colon on the line after the constructor name, as this cleanly separates the member initializer list from the function prototype.Indent your member initializer list, to make it easier to see the function names.If the member initialization list is short/trivial, all initializers can go on one line:Foo(int x, int y)
        : m_x { x }, m_y { y }
    {
